{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"choose","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/XPath/Functions/choose","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div style=\"background:#f5f5f5; margin: 5px 0;\" id=\"sect1\">\n    <b><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/XSLT/Transforming_XML_with_XSLT/The_Netscape_XSLT_XPath_Reference\">XSLT/XPath Reference</a></b>: <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/XSLT/Element\">XSLT elements</a>, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/EXSLT\">EXSLT functions</a>, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/XPath/Functions\">XPath functions</a>, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/XPath/Axes\">XPath axes</a>\n</div>\n<p>The <code>choose</code> function returns one of the specified objects based on a boolean parameter.</p>\n<div class=\"notecard note\" id=\"sect2\">\n  <p><strong>Note:</strong> This method should be used instead of <code>if ()</code>, which has been deprecated.</p>\n</div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":true,"content":"<pre class=\"notranslate\">choose( boolean, object1, object2 )\n</pre>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"arguments","title":"Arguments","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"boolean\"><code>boolean</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>The boolean operation to use when determining which object to return.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"object1\"><code>object1</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>The first object to consider returning.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"object2\"><code>object2</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>The second object to consider returning.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"returns","title":"Returns","isH3":true,"content":"<p>If the boolean parameter is true, the first object is returned; otherwise, the second object is returned.</p>\n<div class=\"notecard note\" id=\"sect3\">\n  <p><strong>Note:</strong> All parameters are evaluated, even the one that's not returned.</p>\n</div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"defined","title":"Defined","isH3":true,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/xforms11/#fn-choose\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">XForms 1.1</a></p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"gecko_support","title":"Gecko support","isH3":true,"content":"<p>Supported.</p>"}}],"toc":[],"summary":"The choose function returns one of the specified objects based on a boolean parameter.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-09-20T02:49:59.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"choose","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"}],"source":{"folder":"en-us/web/xpath/functions/choose","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/xpath/functions/choose/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/309b7e313af4aebde03f5825ec530db614e2bb16","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/XPath","title":"XPath"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/XPath/Functions","title":"Functions"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/XPath/Functions/choose","title":"choose"}],"pageTitle":"choose - XPath | MDN","noIndexing":false}}